\
StartFragment**Peafowl**&nbsp;is a common name for two bird species of the genus&nbsp;[*Pavo*](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pavo_\(genus\))&nbsp;and one species of the closely related genus&nbsp;[*Afropavo*](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afropavo)&nbsp;within the tribe&nbsp;[Pavonini](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pavonini)&nbsp;of the family&nbsp;[Phasianidae](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phasianidae)&nbsp;(the pheasants and their allies). Male peafowl are referred to as&nbsp;**peacocks**, and female peafowl are referred to as&nbsp;**peahens**.EndFragment\
